# 📍 Day 18 — NAT Gateway & Direct Connect

## 🎯 Objective

Understand advanced networking and hybrid connectivity in AWS.

---

## 🌐 NAT Gateway

### 📌 What is NAT Gateway?

* Managed AWS service
* Allows instances in private subnet to access the internet
* Prevents inbound internet traffic

---

### 📌 Key Features

* Highly available within an AZ
* Scalable
* Preferred over NAT Instance

---

## 🔌 AWS Direct Connect

### 📌 What is Direct Connect?

* Dedicated private connection to AWS
* Connects on-premises data center to AWS

---

### 📌 Benefits

* Lower latency
* Stable network performance
* More secure than internet-based connection

---

### 📌 Common Use Cases

* Hybrid cloud architecture
* Enterprise workloads
* Large-scale data transfer

---

## ⚖️ NAT Gateway vs NAT Instance

| Feature      | NAT Gateway | NAT Instance |
| ------------ | ----------- | ------------ |
| Managed      | ✅ Yes       | ❌ No         |
| Scalability  | Automatic   | Manual       |
| Availability | High        | Lower        |

---

## 💡 Key Learnings

* NAT Gateway is modern & preferred solution
* Direct Connect is critical for hybrid cloud setups
* Networking design impacts security and performance

